pt.up.fe.dceg.neptus.imc.lsf

Class LsfIndex

  • java.lang.Object
    • pt.up.fe.dceg.neptus.imc.lsf.LsfIndex

  • public class LsfIndex
extends java.lang.Object
    This class processes a lsf log file and generates a respective index which can be used for a more efficient access to the messages in the log
    Author:
    zp, pdias

      • LsfIndex

        public LsfIndex(java.io.File lsfFile,
        IMCDefinition defs)
         throws java.lang.Exception
        Class constructor. Creates a new index from given lsf File and IMC definitions.
        This method will first look for an lsf.index file and load it. If none is found, the index is generated first.
        Parameters:
        lsfFile - The file, in lsf format with the messages log
        defs - The IMC definitions for that log
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - If the log file is not valid / cannot be read.

      • startReplay

        public void startReplay(long timeMultiplier,
               java.lang.String host,
               int port)
        Just for testing purposes. This method will start broadcasting all messages in the log according to time separations.
        Parameters:
        timeMultiplier - If 1.0 is used, the separation between messages will be approximately the same as real-time. If this value is higher, the replay will be done faster in the same proportion.

        Retrieve the name of an entity for a specific vehicle.
        This method uses the EntityInfo messages in the log to calculate this value.

      • getEntityName

        public java.lang.String getEntityName(int entityId)
        This method uses the EntityInfo messages present in the log to calculate the name the of the given entity id.
        This method should be used only for single vehicle logs. Otherwise #getEntityName(Integer, Integer) should be used instead.
        Parameters:
        entityId - The (numeric) id of the entity to resolve
        Returns:
        The resolved name of the entity
